# Project Rules Research & Draft

## Tech Stack
- Core: Vanilla HTML5, Vanilla CSS3, Vanilla JavaScript.
- Fonts: Inter (Google Fonts).
- Icons: Lucide/SVG based (inline).

## Design System (Tokens)
- Background: `--color-midnight` (#05070a)
- Secondary BG: `--color-deep-blue` (#0a0f1a)
- Accents: 
  - `--color-electric-blue` (#3b82f6)
  - `--color-ubuntu-orange` (#e95420)
- Borders: `--color-border` (rgba(255,255,255,0.05))
- Border Radius: 
  - `--radius-sm`: 4px
  - `--radius-md`: 8px
- Transitions: `--transition` (all 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1))

## Aesthetic Guidelines
- "Native OS" / "Consultancy-grade" minimalist aesthetic.
- "Midnight Navy" palette with "Ubuntu Orange" humanistic accents.
- High-density data visualization (analytical canvas).
- Subtle micro-animations and gradients.
- Glassmorphism/Transparent containers with subtle borders.
- Responsive design: Centered layouts for mobile/tablet.

## Coding Standards
- Use CSS Variables for all colors and design tokens.
- Maintain "No Uppercase Policy" (Sentence case preferred for headers/labels unless specified).
- Semantic HTML5 elements.
- Accessible ARIA labels for interactive components.
- Standardized 6px-8px rounding for consistency.

## Prohibited
- Generic colors (pure red, blue, green).
- TailwindCSS (unless explicitly requested).
- External JS libraries (unless explicitly requested).
- Placeholders (use `generate_image` or SVG).
